# Add mattermost_config to runtime_config; parse channels.mattermost; wire into daemon.ml

## Requirements

- Add `mattermost_config` record to `src/runtime_config.ml`: `{ enabled: bool; host: string; bot_token: string; team_id: string; channel_ids: string list; allow_users: string list }`.
- Add `mattermost: mattermost_config option` to `channel_config`. Parse from `channels.mattermost` JSON in `config_loader.ml`. Required when enabled: `host`, `bot_token`. Defaults: `team_id = ""`, `channel_ids = []`, `allow_users = []`. Yield `None` when disabled or absent.
- In `src/daemon.ml`, if `config.channels.mattermost` is `Some _`, call `Lwt.async (fun () -> Mattermost.start ~config ~session_manager)`. Add `"mattermost"` to `write_state` components.

## Implementation Notes

`host` is the Mattermost server hostname (e.g., `"mattermost.example.com"`), without scheme. The WS URL is constructed as `"wss://" ^ host ^ "/api/v4/websocket"` and REST base as `"https://" ^ host`.

`team_id` is optional — some operations are team-scoped in Mattermost; leave as empty string if not needed for initial implementation.

Follow the `discord_config` pattern (which also has `allow_guilds`/`allow_users`) for the record structure and parsing.

## Acceptance Criteria

Done when:
- `Runtime_config.t` compiles with `mattermost_config option` in `channel_config`.
- Config parses host, bot_token, channel_ids, allow_users correctly.
- Daemon launches Mattermost channel when configured.
- `make test` passes.
